            "style": "",
            "text": "In 1964, the split-window design was discarded for a single-piece rear window, and power was bumped to 375-horsepower. Big block offerings came in the form of 390 and 425-horsepower variants in 1966. Transmission options grew and so did production numbers. 1967 marked the final year of the C2 Corvette and is considered to be one of the best-selling years to date. Many ",
